# Claude Code Global Environment Variables
# Copy to ~/.claude/.env and fill in values
# NEVER commit the actual .env file to git
# Permissions should be 600: chmod 600 ~/.claude/.env

# === API Keys for Projects ===
# KAGGLE_KEY=
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
# AGENTMAIL_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# === Self-Hosted Services ===
# CRAWL4AI_URL=https://crawl.example.com
# CRAWL4AI_TOKEN=
# Supabase (internal/self-hosted): configured via `./setup.sh supabase internal`,
# which stores the connection string in ~/.claude.json. Shape for reference:
#   postgresql://postgres:<password>@your-db-host:5432/postgres

# === Add more API keys below ===

# ============================================================================
# FLEET KNOBS — different destination: copy these into a repo-root `.env`
# (gitignored; the justfile auto-loads it via `set dotenv-load`). Point them
# at YOUR machines — every "macstudio"/"mac" in the docs is an example of
# these values, not a requirement. Without them, node-targeting recipes
# (captain, node-up, attach, ...) assume an ssh alias named "macstudio".
# ============================================================================

# Your always-on node's ssh alias (from your ~/.ssh/config).
# FLEET_NODE=macstudio

# Same node, for herdr-remote: ssh alias (interactive attach) and its
# tailnet/MagicDNS name or IP (control-plane bridge, no ssh).
# HERDR_REMOTE_SSH=macstudio
# HERDR_REMOTE_HOST=mac

# Where the firstmate clone lives on the node (default ~/firstmate).
# FIRSTMATE_DIR=~/firstmate
